Description: The Grundfos Hydro Multi-E 3 CRIE 5-4 booster system transfers and pressure boosts clean water in a range of settings, from waterworks to hotels, hospitals and schools. It is made up of 2 to 3 CME pumps coupled in parallel and mounted on a common base frame made of DIN W.-Nr. 1.4301 stainless steel. The suction side incorporates a DIN W.-Nr. 1.4401 or DIN W.-Nr. 1.4571 suction manifold, pressure switch mounted on a drainable valve and an isolating valve while the discharge side has a non-return valve, isolating valve, pressure gauge, two pressure transmitters on a drainable valve, a diaphragm tank and a stainless steel discharge manifold per DIN W.-Nr. 1.4401 or DIN W.-Nr. 1.4571. Maintaining a constant pressure regardless of flow fluctuation, this system has an internal PI-controller to regulate the number of running pumps and their speed of the pumps according to the required flow.
